                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00 Revolutions/135: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-03T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 3, 1931—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 4—2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. My 81, March 2, 3 p.m.<note n="6" xml:id="d993fn6">Not printed.</note>
                    Diplomatic corps at meeting this morning decided to ignore Sanchez Cerro; to
                    await notification from <pb facs="1031" n="911" xml:id="pg_911"/> Foreign Office
                    as to composition new junta before making any courtesy calls upon members of
                    junta; and that present transitory junta and provisional junta presently to be
                    formed are logical continuation of Sanchez Cerro government.</p>
                <p>Most of colleagues and I feel meeting premature and ill-considered. British and
                    Japanese state they wish to follow our lead regarding recognition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
